# 📦 DTO (Data Transfer Object)

## 📌 What is DTO?
DTO (Data Transfer Object) ဆိုတာ **Layer တစ်ခုကနေ Layer တစ်ခုဆီ Data ပို့ဖို့သုံးတဲ့ Object** ဖြစ်ပါတယ်။

---

## 🧠 Why use DTO?

### ❌ Problem (Without DTO)
```java
User {
  id;
  email;
  password;
}
```
👉 API response မှာ `password` ပါသွားနိုင်တယ် ❗

---

### ✅ Solution (Using DTO)
```java
UserDTO {
  id;
  email;
}
```
👉 Client ကိုလိုအပ်တဲ့ data ပဲ return ပြန်ပေးနိုင်တယ်

---

## 📊 Diagram (Data Flow)
```
Client
  |
  v
Controller
  |
  v
Service Layer
  |
  v
Entity (Database Model)
  |
  | ❌ Do NOT return directly
  v
DTO (Filtered Data)
  |
  v
Client Response
```

---

## 🎯 Benefits of DTO
- 🔒 Hide sensitive fields (e.g. password, token)
- 🧱 Avoid exposing Entity (database structure)
- 🧼 Clean API response
- 🔄 Control data flow (custom request/response)

---

## 🛠️ Example (Spring Boot)

### Entity
```java
@Entity
public class User {
    private Long id;
    private String email;
    private String password;
}
```

### DTO
```java
public class UserDTO {
    private Long id;
    private String email;
}
```

### Mapping
```java
public UserDTO toDTO(User user) {
    UserDTO dto = new UserDTO();
    dto.setId(user.getId());
    dto.setEmail(user.getEmail());
    return dto;
}
```

---

## 🚀 Best Practices
- ✔️ Use separate DTOs for Request & Response  
- ✔️ Never expose Entity directly in Controller  
- ✔️ Do mapping in Service layer  
- ✔️ Use tools like MapStruct / ModelMapper  

---

## 🧩 Summary
👉 DTO = **Safe + Clean way to transfer data between layers**
